    • Method Detail

      • registerCollaborator

        public java.lang.String registerCollaborator(int intType,
                                             java.lang.String fullName,
                                             java.lang.String id,
                                             java.lang.String email,
                                             java.lang.String extension)

        registerCollaborator

        Description: Registers a collaborator based on the provided information and type. This method checks for duplicate collaborators with the same ID using the searchCollaborator(String) method. If there is a duplicate collaborator, it returns a message indicating that the collaborator has already been registered. If there is no duplicate, it checks for available space to register a new collaborator using the availableCollaborator() method. If there is no available space, it returns a message indicating that no more collaborators can be registered. If space is available, it creates a new instance of either ImprovementCollaborator (ImprovementCollaborator.ImprovementCollaborator(String, String, String, String))or general Collaborator (Collaborator.Collaborator(String, String, String, String))based on the provided type. The newly created collaborator is then added to the array of collaborators.

        Preconditions:

        • collaborators array must be initialized.
        • searchCollaborator and availableCollaborator methods should be in place.

        Postconditions:

        • A collaborator is registered based on the provided information and type, and a message indicating the success or failure of the registration is returned.
        Parameters:
        intType - The type of collaborator (1 for DTI, 2 for general).
        fullName - The full name of the collaborator.
        id - The ID of the collaborator.
        email - The email address of the collaborator.
        extension - The extension number of the collaborator.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the success or failure of the registration.

      • registerDepartment

        public java.lang.String registerDepartment(java.lang.String internalCode,
                                           java.lang.String name,
                                           java.lang.String address,
                                           int intResponsibleCollaborator)

        registerDepartment

        Description: Registers a new department in the university system with the provided internal code, name, address, and responsible collaborator.

        Preconditions:

        • internalCode, name, and address must be valid strings.
        • departments array must be initialized.
        • intResponsibleCollaborator must be a valid index representing the responsible collaborator in the list of available collaborators.

        Postconditions:

        • A new department is registered in the university system with the provided internal code, name, address, and responsible collaborator.
        • If there is available space in the departments array, the new department is added to the array.
        Parameters:
        internalCode - The internal code of the department.
        name - The name of the department.
        address - The address of the department.
        intResponsibleCollaborator - The index of the responsible collaborator in the list of available collaborators.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the success of the department registration.

      • searchCollaborator

        public Collaborator searchCollaborator(java.lang.String id)

        searchCollaborator

        Description: Searches for a collaborator with the specified ID. This method iterates through the array of collaborators stored in the university and checks if there is a collaborator with the provided ID. If a collaborator with the matching ID is found, it returns the collaborator object; otherwise, it returns null.

        Preconditions:

        • collaborators array must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • The collaborator object with the specified ID, if found, is returned; otherwise, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the collaborator to search for.
        Returns:
        The collaborator object with the specified ID, if found; otherwise, null.

      • displayCollaborators

        public java.lang.String displayCollaborators()

        displayCollaborators

        Description: Generates a message listing the available collaborators with their full names and IDs. The system loops along all the collaborators until it finds an empty spot. To the other collaborators that were found, their full name and Id is extracted and added to the list.

        Preconditions:

        • collaborators array must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • A message holding a numbered list of the available collaborators with their full names and IDs is generated.
        Returns:
        A message listing the available collaborators with their full names and IDs.

      • availableCollaborator

        public int availableCollaborator()

        availableCollaborator

        Description: Determines the index of the next available slot in the array of collaborators. This method iterates through the array of collaborators stored in the university and returns the index of the first null slot found. If no null slot is found, it returns -1, indicating that there is no available space to register a new collaborator.

        Preconditions:

        • collaborators array must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • The index of the next available slot in the array of collaborators, if found; otherwise, -1 is returned.
        Returns:
        The index of the next available slot in the array of collaborators, if found; otherwise, -1.
